  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0db1\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0db8 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dbb \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"I will go home for Nandalal\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Foreign Affairs and President's Attorney Mr. Ali Sabri said in Parliament today (2) that he is ready to step down on behalf of the Governor of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka, Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe.",
        "Mr. Ali Sabri said this during the second reading debate on the Budget Appropriation Bill.",
        "The Minister of Foreign Affairs who said that he would make a request to everyone not to jump after the Governor of the Central Bank, said that he is a person who has fulfilled what he said.",
        "He said that this is a good budget and the first step in building the country has been taken.",
        "Mr. Ali Sabri also said that all parties are requested to support the implementation of the budget proposals.",
        "The Minister of Foreign Affairs said that since Sri Lanka has gone to the blacklist for non-payment of debt, no one will give loans to the country today and also stated that the country's economic crisis is not the result of what happened yesterday."
      ],
